Situation

Understanding the problem space

The challenge we faced and market context

The Challenge

Lyra started as a collection of standalone AI models, but users were struggling to integrate them into their workflows. Developers had to manage multiple APIs, inconsistent documentation, and fragmented tooling.

Our research showed that 68% of potential users abandoned integration after the initial setup phase due to complexity and lack of cohesive ecosystem support.

Key Pain Points

  • Fragmented developer experience across products
  • Inconsistent API patterns and authentication
  • Lack of unified monitoring and analytics
  • Limited cross-product integration capabilities
Task

2. Design System & Architecture
